name: Ritz Classic Panjim

reviews.review_text:
Warm ambience here. And the fish thali is to die for.
The food comes very fast and nice hospitality.
The beer batter fry squids very lovely..
Do try the like soda if possible
The serradura wasn't thick but rather a little too watery

Ritz Classic Panjim is a legendary Fish Thali place which should be in to-do list of every person visiting Goa. I have been coming here for last 10 years and never disappointed by their Chonak Fish Thali. Mr. Bhaskar Shetty (Manager) is as hospitable as always serving with big smile. However, this time around we had a very bad experience with one of their waiter who is bald. He was extremely rude to all of our queries regarding fish availability and freshness before placing the order, gave weird looks to us and spoilt the entire experince for us due to his rude attitude. Will never come to this place again to see this person for how badly he treated us during our entire meal time and rather visit Ritz's other outlet.

We ordered here very good food. The taste was very nice. However, the downside of it is the crowd here you must stand at least for 30 minutes to get your turn. We were literally pissed off standing so much, however, just because this has that go authentic food so we waited long.
We ordered crab garlic, which was very good and tasted also, nice.
I like too much the fish curry, which was so good to have with the rice. The caramel pudding was not that great, but yeah, fine to eat one time. The soul kadi is must try.

description:
### Dining at Ritz Classic Panjim: A Culinary Gem in Goa

Nestled in the heart of Panjim, Ritz Classic is a celebrated culinary hotspot that has garnered a commendable rating of **4.2** out of **5**, based on **16,759 reviews**. This bustling eatery is well-known for its offerings, especially the **fish thali**, which has become synonymous with authentic Goan fare. Highlighted by robust **tags** such as "thali" (1224 mentions), "Goan" (865 mentions), "crab masala" (87 mentions), and "solkadi" (70 mentions), Ritz Classic Panjim stands out as a must-visit for both locals and travelers seeking to savor the rich flavors of Goa.

### Ambiance & Design

As you step into Ritz Classic, you're greeted by a **warm ambiance** that reflects the spirit of Goan hospitality. The restaurant's **decor** features a blend of traditional charm and contemporary comfort, with earthy tones and rustic wooden accents providing a cozy backdrop. The soft lighting enhances the inviting atmosphere, making it perfect for families and groups. Although the reviews do not specify music, the general vibe indicates a relaxed setting, conducive for enjoying long meals filled with delightful conversations.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

Ritz Classic is best known for its **signature dishes**, particularly the much-lauded **Chonak Fish Thali**, which has been a staple for many patrons over the years. Reviewers consistently rave about the **freshness and flavor**, with mentions of quick service that keeps up with the high demand. The **crab garlic** and the rich **fish curry** served alongside steamed rice have also received high praise for their authentic flavors. The **solkadi**, a kokum and coconut-based drink, is a must-try, as emphasized in the reviews. However, the **caramel pudding** received mixed feedback, with one reviewer noting it was "not that great" but still worth a try.

The **presentation** of the dishes is equally noteworthy, with colorful thalis that not only delight the palate but also please the eyes. The varied textures and vibrant colors in the dishes add to the overall dining experience.

### Customer Experience & Service

Service can be a mixed bag at Ritz Classic, as evidenced by customer reviews. While most patrons commend the **friendly service** and the hospitality offered by the manager, Mr. Bhaskar Shetty, one review pointed out a notable instance of rudeness from a staff member, which marred the experience for that particular group. Despite this isolated incident, the restaurant generally maintains a good reputation for courteous service.

Given its popularity, it’s advisable to expect **crowds**; diners have reported waiting at least **30 minutes** during peak times. However, many opt to endure the wait due to the promise of authentic Goan cuisine that awaits them. While reservations may not be highlighted, arriving early is recommended to minimize wait times.

### Popularity & Reviews

Ritz Classic Panjim enjoys significant social media buzz, with many customers sharing their experiences and calling the restaurant a **legendary Fish Thali place** that should be on every visitor’s checklist. The combination of flavorful food and a lively atmosphere contributes to its enduring popularity. The establishment is clearly a well-loved fixture in the culinary landscape of Goa, attracting repeat visitors year after year.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The charm of Ritz Classic comes alive through customer-shared **photos**. Images showcase beautifully plated dishes filled with rich colors and enticing textures—from the vibrant thali to the perfectly fried squids. These visuals resonate with the descriptions found within reviews, effectively bridging the gap between text and taste, and enabling potential diners to envision their experience before they even step through the doors.

In conclusion, Ritz Classic Panjim is more than just a restaurant; it’s a celebrated institution defined by its authentic Goan cuisine, warm ambiance, and a loyal following. With its focus on **thali** offerings and seafood classics, it promises an unforgettable dining journey for all who visit.
